data.body:
latest on master (2017-08-12)

- open the settings, add
```json
"workbench.colorCustomizations": {
        "statusBar.background": "#7A6969"
}
```
- hover over the color, see that the color picker header shows `"#7A6969"` (including the quotes)
- open a css file, have
```
 --toolbar-title-theme: {
    color: #357C35;
  };
```
- hover over the color. see that color picker header is `#357C35` (no quotes)
- switch back to the json file, hover, now the title is `#7A6969`, without quotes 
-> Should be with quotes again, like the first time we hovered. picking a different color will result in invalid JSON.
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6461412/29241686-ba284a8c-7f7e-11e7-8fd0-afdc98877463.png)

- VSCode Version: 1.15 32bits version
- OS Version: Windows 10 64 bits last version

Steps to Reproduce:

1. Open css (blank)
2. Paste the following code (that I'm using in my project);
```css
@supports (grid-area: auto) {
    @media screen and (min-width: 768px) {
        .me {
            display: grid;
            justify-content: center;
            align-content: space-between;
            grid-template-columns: 60% 40%;
            grid-template-areas: "left right";
            align-items: center;
        }
        .me-text {
            grid-area: left;
        }
        .me-image {
            grid-area: right;
        }
        .gridport {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-rows: 1fr 1fr;
            grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
            grid-template-areas: "upleft upright" "downleft downright";
            justify-content: space-between;
            align-content: space-between;
            grid-column-gap: 20px;
            grid-row-gap: 20px;
        }
        .upleft {
            grid-area: upleft;
        }
        .upright {
            grid-area: upright;
        }
        .downleft {
            grid-area: downleft;
        }
        .downright {
            grid-area: downright;
        }
        .around {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
            justify-content: space-between;
            align-content: space-between;
            grid-template-areas: "up down";
        }
        .about {
            grid-area: up;
        }
        .web {
            grid-area: down;
        }
        @media screen and (min-width: 2200px) {
            .content {
                margin: 90px 20% 0px 20%;
                max-width: 80%;
                width: auto;
            }
            @media screen and (min-width: 3840px) {
                .content {
                    margin: 90px auto 0px auto;
                    max-width: 2648px;
                }
                .gridport {
                    grid-template-rows: auto;
                    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr 1fr 1fr;
                    grid-template-areas: "upleft upright downleft downright";
                }
            }
        }
    }
}
```

3: We can see two bugs:
1- Unexpected unkown rule and expected {} in random parts of the code. Code is perfectly fine and working as expected. See: http://i.imgur.com/TcID5QV.png

2- Grid-area not being colored properly. See; http://i.imgur.com/GNpVAU3.png

Reproduces without extensions: Yes
